		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65496942"><p>The Maunder minimum thing is junk science pushed by denialists.  It happened to overlap with the Little Ice Age in Europe, so they declare it must have been the cause.  But in fact the Little Ice Age started well before the Maunder minimum, and the consensus is that it was caused by volcanic activity.  It also was a local event, not a global one, which argues against it having anything to do sunspot activity.</p></div>
	</div>

